TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi beforefieldinit PropertyMap extends System.Object

Docs.summary: Provides a way to translate property values between Windows Forms controls and Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF) elements.

remarks.format:
## Remarks Use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.PropertyMap> class to define translations between [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_winforms](~/includes/tlasharptla-winforms-md.md)] properties and [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_winclient](~/includes/tlasharptla-winclient-md.md)] properties in a hybrid application. The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ElementHost.PropertyMap%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> and <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.WindowsFormsHost.PropertyMap%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> properties on the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ElementHost> and <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.WindowsFormsHost> classes define mappings from one technology to the other.
For more information, see [Walkthrough: Mapping Properties Using the ElementHost Control](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/ms788740\(v=vs.100\).aspx) and [Walkthrough: Mapping Properties Using the WindowsFormsHost Element](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/ms788729\(v=vs.100\).aspx).
## Examples The following code example shows how to add a mapping for the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.Margin%2A> property to an <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ElementHost> control.
[!code-csharp[PropertyMappingWithElementHost#12](~/samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_Wpf/PropertyMappingWithElementHost/CSharp/PropertyMappingWithElementHost/Form1.cs#12)] [!code-vb[PropertyMappingWithElementHost#12](~/samples/snippets/visualbasic/VS_Snippets_Wpf/PropertyMappingWithElementHost/VisualBasic/PropertyMappingWithElementHost/Form1.vb#12)]
The following code example shows how to replace the default mapping for the <xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.FlowDirection%2A> property on a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.WindowsFormsHost> control.

Docs.param: The name of the property to restore.
Docs.summary: Restores the default property mapping for the given property.

remarks.format:
## Remarks The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.PropertyMap.Reset%2A> method has the following effects on the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.PropertyMap>.
- A default property mapping that has been removed is restored.
- A property mapping that has been added is removed.
- A default property mapping that has been overridden is restored to its default value.
